## 🖥️ Display Configuration (Phase 1 – Working)

The display is a **7‑inch 1024 × 600 IPS panel** driven by an **EK79007 MIPI‑DSI bridge IC**. The working configuration was derived from the Elecrow reference code (`bsp_illuminate.c`) and verified step‑by‑step.

### MIPI‑DSI Bus

```c
esp_lcd_dsi_bus_config_t bus_cfg = {
    .bus_id             = 0,
    .num_data_lanes     = 2,              // 2 data lanes
    .phy_clk_src        = MIPI_DSI_PHY_CLK_SRC_DEFAULT,
    .lane_bit_rate_mbps = 900,           // 900 Mbps per lane
};
ESP_ERROR_CHECK(esp_lcd_new_dsi_bus(&bus_cfg, &dsi_bus));
```

### DBI Command Interface

```c
esp_lcd_dbi_io_config_t dbi_cfg = {
    .virtual_channel = 0,
    .lcd_cmd_bits    = 8,
    .lcd_param_bits  = 8,
};
ESP_ERROR_CHECK(esp_lcd_new_panel_io_dbi(dsi_bus, &dbi_cfg, &mipi_dbi_io));
```

### DPI Video Configuration

```c
